{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> τοιγάρ</b>, <br /> an inferential Particle, <b>therefore, accordingly, well then,</b> κέλεαί με.. μυθήσασθαι μῆνιν Ἀπόλλωνος.. · τοιγὰρ ἐγὼν ἐρέω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.76, compare 10.427, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.254, 8.402, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 309, “Th.” 1038, “Pers.” 607, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 931 (_anapaest meter_), 994, “Aj.” 666, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; rare in Comedy texts [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 516 (_anapaest meter_), 901, 902) and Prose (5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.114, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ καρδίης” 10 (assuming variant))\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; never in <i>Attic dialect</i> Prose. <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> strengthened by other Particles, <b>τοιγαροῦν</b>, <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>τοιγαρῶν</b>, <b>for that very reason, therefore,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.149, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 234e, 246b, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.9.9, +others, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.40, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1271b3, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also in Poets, as [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 490, “OT” 1519 (troch.), “Ph.” 341, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1098, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>τοιγάρτοι</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.3, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.38, 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.108, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 82d, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; rare in Poets, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 145, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 654 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 643 (_anapaest meter_):— 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus always inserts a word between τοιγάρ\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] and τοι, τοιγὰρ ἐγώ τοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.413, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.179, 214, +others\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] —These forms must begin the sentence, except in late Gr., where τοιγαροῦν may be postponed, as [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Cleomedes Astronomus 1.8, Wilcken “Chr.” 491.7 (2nd c.AD), 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “περὶ τῆς τάξεως τῶν ἰδίων βιβλίων” 2, Vett. Val. 356.3, “Sammelb.” 6222.12 (3rd c.AD), 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Caesares” 318d. (It is doubtful whether τοι- contains the _demonstrative_ stem το-.) \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5105","accentedUnicode":"τοιγαροῦν","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1063","matchingForm":"γάρ","stepTransliteration":"gar","gloss":"for","_zh_tw_Gloss":"因為","_es_Gloss":"porque ","_zh_Gloss":"因为"},{"strongNumber":"G3767","matchingForm":"οὖν","stepTransliteration":"oun","gloss":"therefore/then","_zh_tw_Gloss":"所以","_es_Gloss":"por tanto/entonces","_zh_Gloss":"所以"},{"strongNumber":"G5104","matchingForm":"τοί","stepTransliteration":"toi","gloss":"certainly","_zh_tw_Gloss":"只是","_es_Gloss":"ciertamente","_zh_Gloss":"只是"}],"shortDef":"therefore, then","mediumDef":"therefore, then <br /><b>well then, so then, wherefore, for that reason,</b> <ref='1Th.4.8'>1Thess. 4:8;</ref> <ref='Heb.12.1'>Heb. 12:1</ref>*","stepGloss":"therefore","stepTransliteration":"toigaroun","count":2,"_es_Definition":"asi pues, por lo tanto, entonces, por esa misma razón","_zh_tw_Definition":"為此理由, 因此, 所以 (帖前4:8;來12:1)","_zh_Definition":"为此理由, 因此, 所以 (帖前4:8;来12:1)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"thế nên; vì thế; do đó","_zh_tw_Gloss":"所以","_es_Gloss":"por lo tanto","_zh_Gloss":"所以"}]}